This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with sentiment analysis in text. It also involves the use of word2vec, which is a popular technique in natural language processing. It could also be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves the use of a distributed language model. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as sentiment analysis is often used in search engines to improve the relevance of search results. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possibility as sentiment analysis is a common application of AI. Finally, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) could be a relevant sub-category as sentiment analysis is often used in social media analysis.
